<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A staffer for Donald Trump is under fire for mocking Joe Biden as he visited the graves of his late family members over the weekend. </p>

<p>On Sunday Francis Brennan, Trump's campaign director of strategic response, slammed Biden for not speaking to media, as he walked through Brandywine church's cemetery in Wilmington, Delaware, where his late son Beau is buried along with his first wife Neilia and their daughter Naomi.</p>

<p>Brennan tweeted video of of Biden walking through the cemetery. A reporter is heard saying: 'Mr. Vice President come talk to us!' and Biden responds with a cheerful wave before walking along to pay his respects to his loved ones.</p>

<p>Brennan sarcastically captioned the video: 'Joe Biden just keeps meandering along.'</p>

<p>Francis Brennan, Trump's campaign director of strategic response, mocked Joe Biden on Twitter on Sunday as he visited the graves of his loved ones. He said that 'Joe Biden just keeps meandering along' when reporters asked to speak with him. Biden politely waved to reporters in the clip</p>

<p>On Sunday Biden attended church then visited Brandywine church's cemetery in Wilmington, Delaware, where his late son Beau is buried along with his first wife Neilia and their daughter Naomi</p>

<p>Beau Biden, the former Delaware attorney general and an Iraq veteran, died from brain cancer in 2015 at the age of 46. Neila and Naomi Biden died in a car accident in 1972.</p>

<p>The incident came days after it was revealed the president allegedly refused to visit a war cemetery in Paris back in 2018 and said Americans who died in wars were 'losers' and 'suckers' – but Trump denies the report.</p>

<p>As Biden attended church and visited his loved ones, Trump spent Saturday and Sunday playing golf at the Trump National Golf Club in Sterling, Virginia.</p>

<p>Brennan’s tweet was met with bitter backlash by Twitter users to said he was disrespecting Biden in his emotional visit to his family's graves. </p>

<p>'He is visiting his son’s grave. Are you even human!!' Mia Farrow replied.</p>

<p>Biden pictured leaving St. Joseph on the Brandywine Roman Catholic Church after attending Sunday services to visit his loved ones' graves. Though he didn't speak to reporters he greeted them with a wave before walking on </p>

<p>Beau Biden, the former Delaware attorney general and an Iraq veteran, died from brain cancer in 2015 at the age of 46</p>

<p>Joe Biden's first wife Neila and their daughter Naomi Biden died in a car accident in 1972. Biden and his wife Neilia pictured above cutting his 30th birthday cake at a party in Wilmington </p>

<p>As Biden visited his loved ones, Donald Trump spent the weekend playing golf. Pictured talking on the phone as he returns to the White House Sunday afternoon after spending time at the Trump National Golf Club in Sterling, Virginia</p>

<p>'Despicable you would even try to make this a story. He’s visiting his son’s grave and no one, with any humanity left in them, would expect him to make it into a PR event. It actually notches up my respect for him even more. Shame on you,' another Twitter user added.</p>

<p>'This is the Director of Strategic Response for the Trump campaign mocking Joe Biden for walking through the graveyard where his son is buried after leaving church this morning while Donald Trump spent his day on the golf course,' Andrew Weinstein, chair of the Democrats Lawyers’ Council said.</p>

<p>One user shared a video of Donald Trump actually meandering, walking around a lawn aimlessly avoiding reporters.</p>

<p>'Walking in a straight line is not meandering. Get a grip,' one Twitter user clapped back.</p>

<p>'Meandering, as one does while visiting one’s child’s grave. Where do they find little p****s like you, Francis?' another social media user added.</p>

<p>Biden's sentimental visit to his family's graves comes after news broke that the president allegedly refused to visit the graves of american war heroes in France in 2018. </p>

<p>On Thursday the Atlantic reported that the president allegedly dismissed a visit to the Aisne-Marne American Cemetery near Paris, saying 'why should I go to that cemetery? It’s filled with losers.'</p>

<p>Twitter users slammed Brennan for trying to mock Biden as he visited his family's graves</p>

<p>Mia Farrow admonished Brennan saying: 'He is visiting his son's grave. Are you even human!!'</p>

<p>Andrew Weinstein, chair of the Democrats Lawyers’ Council noted that Brennan was disrespecting Biden for visiting his family's graves as Trump spent his day on the golf course</p>

